uld also consider using a static method, although it's probably unnecessary. The goal is to ensure the functionality where only the call sites generate the class. It’s likely I need to cover the target class methods and the interface methods too.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Checking code requirements**\\n\\nI shouldn’t use reflection directly—sounds like a plan! I think I just need to focus on using source context for examples instead. I also need to verify if checkstyle applies, maybe checking line lengths. And then there's the matter of type annotations for variables in Java. Looks like I need to write everything into a file as well. I'll keep these points in mind as I work through this!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_lHqZQVs394aeXRukQDiDZw6X|fc_0268ff255d4cec2c0169fb8034af88819cabfb80f6759511a4", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/cglib/cglib-nodep/2.2.2/src/test/java/cglib/cglib_nodep/MethodDelegateInnerGeneratorTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage cglib.cglib_nodep;\n\nimport net.sf.cglib.core.CodeGenerationException;\nimport net.sf.cglib.reflect.MethodDelegate;\nimport org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class MethodDelegateInnerGeneratorTest {\n\n    @Test\n    void createsDelegateForInstanceMethodWithMatchingInterfaceSignature() {\n        GreetingTarget target = new GreetingTarget(\"Hello\");\n\n        try {\n            GreetingOperation delegate = (GreetingOperation) MethodDelegate.create(\n                    target,\n                    \"formatGreeting\",\n                    GreetingOperation.class\n            );\n\n            assertThat(delegate.greet(\"Ada\")).isEqualTo(\"Hello, Ada\");\n            assertThat(((MethodDelegate) delegate).getTarget()).isSameAs(target);\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            if (findUnsupportedFeatureError(error) == null) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n        } catch (CodeGenerationException exception) {\n            Error error = findUnsupportedFeatureError(exception);\n            if (error == null) {\n                throw exception;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void createsDelegateForStaticMethodWithMatchingInterfaceSignature() {\n        try {\n            GreetingOperation delegate = (GreetingOperation) MethodDelegate.createStatic(\n                    GreetingTarget.class,\n                    \"formatStaticGreeting\",\n                    GreetingOperation.class\n            );\n\n            assertThat(delegate.greet(\"Grace\")).isEqualTo(\"Static hello, Grace\");\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            if (findUnsupportedFeatureError(error) == null) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n        } catch (CodeGenerationException exception) {\n            Error error = findUnsupportedFeatureError(exception);\n            if (error == null) {\n                throw exception;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static Error findUnsupportedFeatureError(Throwable throwable) {\n        Throwable current = throwable;\n        while (current != null) {\n            if (current instanceof Error error && NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                return error;\n            }\n            current = current.getCause();\n        }\n        return null;\n    }\n\n    public interface GreetingOperation {\n        String greet(String name);\n    }\n\n    public static class GreetingTarget {\n        private final String prefix;\n\n        GreetingTarget(String prefix) {\n            this.prefix = prefix;\n        }\n\n        public String formatGreeting(String name) {\n            return prefix + \", \" + name;\n        }\n\n        public static String formatStaticGreeting(String name) {\n            return \"Static hello, \" + name;\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2487, "output": 1991, "cacheRead": 15360, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 19838, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778090017197, "responseId": "resp_0268ff255d4cec2c0169fb8021ef50819ca2faa9ec7dab213d"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_lHqZQVs394aeXRukQDiDZw6X|fc_0268ff255d4cec2c0169fb8034af88819cabfb80f6759511a4", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 3026 bytes to tests/src/cglib/cglib-nodep/2.2.2/src/test/java/cglib/cglib_nodep/MethodDelegateInnerGeneratorTest.java"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1778090044406}]}
